    - ["as3196030", operator.contains, [asyncio.LifoQueue.__dict__,        "__rshift__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __pow__, __lshift__, __rshift__ across all 10 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 10 classes x 3 methods = 30 rows.
# __pow__:    false for all 10 — exponentiation is not defined for any asyncio type.
# __lshift__: false for all 10 — left-shift is not defined for any asyncio type.
# __rshift__: false for all 10 — right-shift is not defined for any asyncio type.
# All 30 values are false.
# asyncio types are designed for coroutine-based concurrency — their entire
#   API surface is expressed through await, async with, async for, and explicit
#   method calls. Arithmetic and bitwise operators (**,  <<, >>) are entirely
#   absent from the asyncio type hierarchy.
# asyncio.Queue note: although Queue is a data structure with a count (qsize()),
#   it defines no arithmetic, bitwise, or collection-operator protocol. Items are
#   inserted with put() and removed with get() — no operator overloading.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore note: these track an integer internal counter
#   (the permit count), yet define no arithmetic operators — the counter is managed
#   exclusively through acquire()/release() coroutines.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

